{
  "text": "Irradiance and prediction of saturating (I sat ) and compensating (I comp ) irradiances for eelgrass: To convert percentage reductions in irradiance by algal producers to absolute values, we needed to apply irradiance at the air-water interface. Surface irradiance data for the annual cycle were provided by R. Payne of Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution. Based on previous measurements in Waquoit Bay throughout a variety of weather conditions, we assumed a surface reflectance of 35% [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "128545999"
